Eagle's Resolve						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Iron Will									PRETEXT:Member of the Eagle Knights.				DESC:You are resolute in your opposition to slavery and oppression, and the very thought of mental control disgusts you.					SOURCEPAGE:p.28				BENEFIT:You receive a +1 bonus on saving throws against mind-affecting effects. When you succeed at such a saving throw, you gain a +2 morale bonus on all attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws for a number of rounds equal to the effect's spell's level, or if the effect is not a spell, one-third the Hit Dice of the creature behind the effect.
Expert Boarder						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																		PRETEXT:Member of the Gray Corsairs.				DESC:You are as comfortable swinging from a rope or dangling from a ship's rigging as you are on stable land.							SOURCEPAGE:p.32				BENEFIT:Acrobatics and Climb are class skills for you. You gain a +2 bonus on Acrobatics and Climb checks to climb or swing on a rope or ship's rigging. You do not provoke attacks of opportunity from climbing or swinging on a rope or ship's rigging.					CSKILL:Acrobatics|Climb	
Falcon's Cry						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_CHA,13										PRETEXT:Member of the Steel Falcons.				DESC:You can inspire those around you to throw off the shackles of oppression, both physical and supernatural.							SOURCEPAGE:p.30				BENEFIT:You can inspire a zeal for freedom in your allies. As a standard action, you can grant everyone within 60 feet who is able to see and hear you the ability to roll twice when attempting an Escape Artist check, a Will save against compulsions, or a Strength check to break chains, manacles, or similar bonds. Such checks must be attempted before the beginning of your next turn.  You can do this %1 times per day.|1+TL
Legionnaire's Inspiration				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																		PRETEXT:Member of the Golden Legion.				DESC:You can inspire your comrades-in-arms to stand against impossible odds.													SOURCEPAGE:p.29				BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can grant all allies within 60 feet who are able to see and hear you a +1 morale bonus to Armor Class for %1 rounds. You can do this %2 times per day.|max(1,CHA)|1+TL
Primal Ancestry						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_WIS,13										PRETEXT:Member of the Primordial Ones.				DESC:You have a deep connection to the primal First World and can channel this link into powerful effects once a day.						SOURCEPAGE:p.34				BENEFIT:Once per day as a move action, you can tap into the essence of the First World, and gain DR 5/cold iron for 1 minute. If you have 11 or more Hit Dice, this increases to DR 10/cold iron. Additionally, while under this effect, enchantment spells you cast gain a +1 bonus to caster level.
Secret Capital						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13										PRETEXT:Member of the Seven Houses.					DESC:You have access to family connections and secret funds you can use to make things happen more easily.								SOURCEPAGE:p.35				BENEFIT:When you use gp to buy capital using the downtime rules (Ultimate Campaign 76), you pay only 75%% of the normal cost.
Strongarm							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Intimidating Prowess								PRETEXT:Member of the Lumber Consortium.				DESC:You are experienced at long-term intimidation of those you wish to exploit, and strike fear into the hearts of those you bully.			SOURCEPAGE:p.33				BENEFIT:When you use the Intimidate skill to improve a target's attitude, if your check result exceeds the DC by 5 or more, the target's attitude is improved for 5d6 hours. During this time, should it attack you, the target immediately becomes shaken for 1d6+1 rounds, as though it had been demoralized.
Twilight Tattoo						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_WIS,13										PRETEXT:Member of the Twilight Talons.				DESC:You have a special tattoo that identifies you as a Twilight Talon when you speak a designated command word.							SOURCEPAGE:p.31				BENEFIT:You gain an invisible magical tattoo that identifies you as a Twilight Talon. When you speak the command word, the tattoo becomes visible for 1 round before fading again. The tattoo has no magical aura when not visible and is not an illusion; it can't be observed through magical means. Additionally, you gain a +2 bonus on Disguise checks and Sleight of Hand checks to hide small objects on your person, and a +2 bonus on all Will saving throws against attempts to scry upon you or read your mind.
